VSaraswathi Vidyalayam, managed with the  patronage of  BHEL,  organised Carnatic music concerts for two days at the Sath Sangham, Bala Ganapathy temple complex, Kailasapuram, Tiruchi.On the inaugural day,  Srilatha and Sowmya presented a pleasing concert in a sampradhaya kutcheri format.Captivating renditionSrilatha and Sowmya, both Sangeetha Sri awardees, captivated the audience by rendering compositions of saint Tyagaraja, Muthuswami Dikshitar and Papanasam Sivan.Shertalai V. M. Sathyamoorthy on the violin and Balaji on the mridangam provided able support.On the second  day, Subha Ganesan, whose lineage can be traced back to Karaikkudi Veenai Sambasiva Iyer, presented a performance.She sang Papanasam Sivan's  "Parvathi Nayagane'' in  Shanmugapriya, which was well received.She was accompanied on the violin by Kandadevi Vijayaraghavan and on the mridangam by Karaikkudi Ganesan.Both the programmes were well attended by the residents of the  township.SYED MUTHAHAR SAQAFBottom Template Starts
